00:00:00.910 --> 00:00:06.220
We're on problem 63.

00:00:06.220 --> 00:00:10.130
Carlotta can drive from her home
to her office by one of

00:00:10.130 --> 00:00:11.800
two possible routes.

00:00:11.800 --> 00:00:15.370
If she must also return by one
of these routes, what is the

00:00:15.370 --> 00:00:17.620
distance of the shorter route?

00:00:17.620 --> 00:00:21.480
So essentially she has a long
route to go to her office,

00:00:21.480 --> 00:00:24.820
that's her home, that's
her office.

00:00:24.820 --> 00:00:27.820
And then she has a short route,
with fewer curves,

00:00:27.820 --> 00:00:29.510
that's my guess.

00:00:29.510 --> 00:00:33.380
And she can go and come
back by one of two--

00:00:33.380 --> 00:00:38.220
Statement number one: when she
drives from her home to her

00:00:38.220 --> 00:00:41.020
office by the shorter route
and returns by the longer

00:00:41.020 --> 00:00:43.800
route, she drives a total
of 42 kilometers.

00:00:43.800 --> 00:00:46.690
So when she goes this, way
shorter route this way and

00:00:46.690 --> 00:00:50.500
then longer route back,
it's 42 kilometers.

00:00:50.500 --> 00:00:56.490
So shorter plus longer
is equal to 42.

00:00:56.490 --> 00:00:59.160
And that by itself doesn't let
me know what the distance of

00:00:59.160 --> 00:01:01.380
the shorter route is.

00:01:01.380 --> 00:01:05.459
Statement number two: when she
drives both ways from her home

00:01:05.459 --> 00:01:08.790
to her office and back by the
longer route, she drives a

00:01:08.790 --> 00:01:10.890
total of 46 kilometers.

00:01:10.890 --> 00:01:13.350
So if she goes by the longer
route and then by the longer

00:01:13.350 --> 00:01:18.250
route again, so 2 times a longer
route is equal to 46

00:01:18.250 --> 00:01:20.000
kilometers.

00:01:20.000 --> 00:01:23.020
Well, this by itself helps me
figure out what the longer

00:01:23.020 --> 00:01:25.090
route is, but they want to
know the distance of the

00:01:25.090 --> 00:01:25.560
shorter route.

00:01:25.560 --> 00:01:28.380
So this, I could just eyeball
this, the longer route is 23

00:01:28.380 --> 00:01:29.240
kilometers.

00:01:29.240 --> 00:01:31.100
But if you want to know the
distance of the shorter route

00:01:31.100 --> 00:01:34.960
you would need this information
as well.

00:01:34.960 --> 00:01:38.100
The shorter route plus
23 is equal to 42.

00:01:38.100 --> 00:01:40.510
So the shorter route
is 19 kilometers.

00:01:40.510 --> 00:01:42.200
So you need both of
the statements.

00:01:42.200 --> 00:01:44.070
Both statements are sufficient,
but one by

00:01:44.070 --> 00:01:46.590
themselves are not enough
to figure out what the

00:01:46.590 --> 00:01:47.370
shorter route is.

00:01:47.370 --> 00:01:49.000
If they ask for the longer
route, just statement two

00:01:49.000 --> 00:01:50.890
could have been good enough.

00:01:50.890 --> 00:01:52.300
