00:01:52.300 --> 00:01:54.780
64.

00:01:54.780 --> 00:01:56.050
Is x greater than y?

00:02:01.470 --> 00:02:04.770
My computer's updating
something.

00:02:04.770 --> 00:02:08.500
It's a little bit-- Is
x greater than y?

00:02:08.500 --> 00:02:17.580
Statement number one tells us
that x is equal to y plus 2.

00:02:17.580 --> 00:02:18.880
Well, let me think about that.

00:02:18.880 --> 00:02:22.820
No matter what y is, x is
going to be 2 more.

00:02:22.820 --> 00:02:25.610
Even if y is a negative million,
x is still going to

00:02:25.610 --> 00:02:26.650
be a bigger number.

00:02:26.650 --> 00:02:29.460
It's going to be 2 more than
negative a million.

00:02:29.460 --> 00:02:31.780
If it's y is negative 10,
this will be negative 8.

00:02:31.780 --> 00:02:34.500
No matter what x will
be greater than y.

00:02:34.500 --> 00:02:37.700
So statement one
is sufficient.

00:02:37.700 --> 00:02:50.322
Statement number two: x/2
is equal to y minus 1.

00:02:50.322 --> 00:02:50.730
OK.

00:02:50.730 --> 00:02:52.810
This doesn't look
as clear there.

00:02:52.810 --> 00:02:56.640
So x is equal to 2y minus 2.

00:02:56.640 --> 00:02:59.200
So we just have to come up with
a condition, one y where

00:02:59.200 --> 00:03:02.770
y is less than x and another y
where y is greater than x and

00:03:02.770 --> 00:03:03.950
then we would have
proven our point.

00:03:03.950 --> 00:03:05.060
So let's think about it.

00:03:05.060 --> 00:03:09.590
When y is 0-- this is using
statement number two-- when y

00:03:09.590 --> 00:03:11.180
is 0, what's x?

00:03:11.180 --> 00:03:14.220
x is minus 2.

00:03:14.220 --> 00:03:18.970
So that's a statement where
y is greater than x.

00:03:18.970 --> 00:03:25.030
And then when y is equal
to 10, what's x?

00:03:25.030 --> 00:03:27.840
x is 18.

00:03:27.840 --> 00:03:32.370
So this is a statement where
y is less than x.

00:03:32.370 --> 00:03:35.060
So statement number two actually
tells us nothing

00:03:35.060 --> 00:03:39.060
about whether x is greater than
y or y is greater than x.

00:03:39.060 --> 00:03:40.540
So statement number
two is useless.

00:03:40.540 --> 00:03:44.660
Statement number one, alone,
is sufficient.

