00:09:18.190 --> 00:09:21.170
67.

00:09:21.170 --> 00:09:23.810
What is the value of b plus c?

00:09:28.220 --> 00:09:41.050
Alright, number one: they tell
us that ab plus cd plus ac

00:09:41.050 --> 00:09:45.410
plus bd is equal to 6.

00:09:45.410 --> 00:09:47.400
And this by itself doesn't help
us much because there's

00:09:47.400 --> 00:09:50.320
all these a's and d's here and
they could be anything.

00:09:50.320 --> 00:09:52.670
So we can't solve
for b plus c.

00:09:52.670 --> 00:09:55.020
But I'm already suspecting that
we could factor out the

00:09:55.020 --> 00:09:56.820
a's and d's somewhere.

00:09:56.820 --> 00:10:00.150
So we can factor out the b's
plus c's, then we might be

00:10:00.150 --> 00:10:02.770
able to figure out the numbers
if we're given more

00:10:02.770 --> 00:10:04.920
information about a and d.

00:10:04.920 --> 00:10:07.260
Statement two, and they give
us more information about a

00:10:07.260 --> 00:10:10.255
and d. a plus d is equal to 4.

00:10:10.255 --> 00:10:12.830
So let me see if I can simplify
this top one.

00:10:12.830 --> 00:10:16.080
Let me see if I can factor out
a bunch of b plus c's.

00:10:16.080 --> 00:10:20.370
So if we think about
it, let me think.

00:10:20.370 --> 00:10:24.030
So if you take this term and
that term and you factor out

00:10:24.030 --> 00:10:29.830
the a you get a-- let me do it
in a different color-- so this

00:10:29.830 --> 00:10:37.910
term and that term is equal to a
times what? b plus c, right?

00:10:37.910 --> 00:10:40.750
You can multiply that out
and you get ab plus ac.

00:10:40.750 --> 00:10:42.720
And then plus, and let's
do the same thing

00:10:42.720 --> 00:10:45.590
with this term, d.

00:10:45.590 --> 00:10:49.170
That's d times c plus b.

00:10:49.170 --> 00:10:53.180
But we can switch the order,
b plus c-- and if you don't

00:10:53.180 --> 00:10:55.540
believe me that this equals
this, multiply it out.

00:10:55.540 --> 00:10:59.340
All I did is I grouped the ab
and the ac terms and then

00:10:59.340 --> 00:11:04.120
factored out the a and then I
grouped the cd and the bd

00:11:04.120 --> 00:11:06.150
terms and factored out the d.

00:11:06.150 --> 00:11:10.190
And then now we can factor
out a b plus c.

00:11:10.190 --> 00:11:13.730
We can do the reverse
distributive property again.

00:11:13.730 --> 00:11:21.615
So now this equals a plus
d times b plus c, right?

00:11:21.615 --> 00:11:24.380
And if you don't believe me,
just multiply b plus c times a

00:11:24.380 --> 00:11:27.800
and then b plus c times d
and you get that, right?

00:11:27.800 --> 00:11:29.740
That's just the distributive
property.

00:11:29.740 --> 00:11:32.820
But now we're ready to solve
because they told us that this

00:11:32.820 --> 00:11:37.630
thing's equal to 6 and they
tell us that this thing is

00:11:37.630 --> 00:11:39.760
equal to 4.

00:11:39.760 --> 00:11:43.980
So b plus c is going to be equal
to 6/4 or 1 and 1/2.

00:11:43.980 --> 00:11:44.950
And we're done.

00:11:44.950 --> 00:11:47.070
You need both statements
together.

00:11:47.070 --> 00:11:48.940
Both statements, together,
are sufficient

00:11:48.940 --> 00:11:51.000
to solve this problem.

